1
00:00:07,220 --> 00:00:11,820
♪She looks at the bright moon
hanging high above the clouds♪

2
00:00:11,860 --> 00:00:14,140
♪And I fall into the mountains♪

3
00:00:14,220 --> 00:00:16,100
♪Protect this broken world♪

4
00:00:16,180 --> 00:00:20,620
♪A faint wish♪

5
00:00:20,660 --> 00:00:23,900
♪Life is just a dream,
isn't the world so?♪

6
00:00:23,980 --> 00:00:27,620
♪Looking back,
I count the joys of my remaining years♪

7
00:00:27,700 --> 00:00:31,020
♪It's difficult to see you in my dreams♪

8
00:00:31,060 --> 00:00:33,940
♪Ignoring the coldness of the world,
I still linger♪

9
00:00:33,980 --> 00:00:37,300
♪Love and hate are intertwined,
not just in the past♪

10
00:00:37,340 --> 00:00:40,900
♪The past is painful,
and time goes by in a flash♪

11
00:00:40,940 --> 00:00:44,500
♪Stars fall on the mountain top again♪

12
00:00:44,580 --> 00:00:48,140
♪My heart is as pure as the moon
and connected to you♪

13
00:00:54,140 --> 00:00:56,980
[No One But You]

14
00:00:56,980 --> 00:00:58,620
[Episode 24]

15
00:00:58,620 --> 00:01:01,980
[We lurk in the dark
so more people can live in the light.]

16
00:01:02,260 --> 00:01:04,260
We caught a rebel

17
00:01:04,260 --> 00:01:05,620
who has

18
00:01:06,060 --> 00:01:07,020
the name

19
00:01:07,420 --> 00:01:09,460
of a high-level undercover agent.

20
00:01:10,180 --> 00:01:12,060
He should only be Guzhou.

21
00:01:23,420 --> 00:01:26,060
Someone who calls
all the shots in Beizhou.

22
00:01:26,060 --> 00:01:27,260
Who else could it be?

23
00:01:31,380 --> 00:01:32,780
Am I Guzhou now?

24
00:01:33,500 --> 00:01:34,660
What are you waiting for then?

25
00:01:48,940 --> 00:01:50,140
So,

26
00:01:51,220 --> 00:01:52,780
I am Guzhou too?

27
00:01:57,420 --> 00:01:59,060
Let's have a look.

28
00:01:59,540 --> 00:02:00,820
Get ready.

29
00:02:01,380 --> 00:02:02,380
I'll wait for you.

30
00:02:24,820 --> 00:02:26,780
The Marshal didn't call you out.

31
00:02:27,220 --> 00:02:28,420
Could it be

32
00:02:28,700 --> 00:02:29,660
a test?

33
00:02:33,940 --> 00:02:35,780
Perhaps the traitor
hasn't spilled everything.

34
00:02:37,500 --> 00:02:38,900
We can turn the tables,

35
00:02:39,380 --> 00:02:40,780
but I should get ready just in case.

36
00:02:56,020 --> 00:02:58,340
♪A drizzle softly falls
in the deep night♪

37
00:02:58,620 --> 00:03:00,900
♪Awakening the jasmine from its slumber♪

38
00:03:02,460 --> 00:03:04,700
♪Two swallows are building
their nest on the beam♪

39
00:03:04,860 --> 00:03:06,260
♪Bringing new mud in their beaks♪

40
00:03:06,260 --> 00:03:07,300
You

41
00:03:09,260 --> 00:03:11,460
have many promises to fulfill.

42
00:03:11,460 --> 00:03:13,060
♪Where fragrant grass
is growing lush and thick♪

43
00:03:13,060 --> 00:03:14,260
I don't allow you to die.

44
00:03:14,260 --> 00:03:19,220
♪Such a beautiful view
is nothing without you♪

45
00:03:21,380 --> 00:03:22,300
I know.

46
00:03:22,900 --> 00:03:23,780
I remember them all.

47
00:03:23,780 --> 00:03:25,420
♪Making the pond water ripple♪

48
00:03:25,420 --> 00:03:26,860
How could I die?

49
00:03:26,860 --> 00:03:31,100
♪I fear most when the full moon occurs♪

50
00:03:31,820 --> 00:03:33,340
♪We share a smile♪

51
00:03:33,420 --> 00:03:35,300
♪But hide the traces
of our acquaintance♪

52
00:03:35,300 --> 00:03:35,660
Wait for...

53
00:03:35,660 --> 00:03:36,580
I'll wait for you.

54
00:03:38,340 --> 00:03:40,300
♪Even if my emotions run deep♪

55
00:03:40,660 --> 00:03:43,140
♪How much would you know?♪

56
00:03:43,300 --> 00:03:45,900
♪I gave you a branch of jasmine♪

57
00:03:46,180 --> 00:03:49,660
♪Wishing you would never leave,
staying with me from dawn to dusk♪

58
00:03:49,740 --> 00:03:52,340
♪I never thought we'd part so easily♪

59
00:03:52,380 --> 00:03:55,780
♪While spending forever meeting again♪

60
00:03:55,820 --> 00:03:58,260
♪Why would I not be happy seeing you?♪

61
00:03:58,380 --> 00:04:02,380
♪Willow fluff flew around the city
when we met in haste♪

62
00:04:02,580 --> 00:04:03,060
See you.

63
00:04:03,060 --> 00:04:07,700
♪Falling into a dream,
I can still remember this love♪

64
00:04:21,260 --> 00:04:23,980
♪I have tasted all the medicines
in the world♪

65
00:04:24,060 --> 00:04:27,340
♪You are the best
that comes with a true heart♪

66
00:04:27,420 --> 00:04:30,140
♪I was aloof, but since I met you♪

67
00:04:30,220 --> 00:04:33,500
♪My deep love for you
can never heal on its own♪

68
00:04:33,620 --> 00:04:36,140
♪Every time I get closer♪

69
00:04:36,380 --> 00:04:40,660
♪My heart flutters
and I let myself get lost in obsession♪

70
00:04:41,170 --> 00:04:42,150
[Potassium cyanide]

71
00:04:42,150 --> 00:04:46,980
♪Catching the tiniest sound in my ears,
I know it is you♪

72
00:04:46,980 --> 00:04:48,820
I knew this would happen.

73
00:04:55,180 --> 00:04:56,860
Don't worry. Just say it.

74
00:04:57,460 --> 00:04:59,380
Who is the high-level undercover agent?

75
00:04:59,900 --> 00:05:01,500
It's him.

76
00:05:01,500 --> 00:05:03,100
Jiang Mohan is Guzhou!

77
00:05:07,100 --> 00:05:07,900
Is that so?

78
00:05:10,140 --> 00:05:11,140
Let me ask you.

79
00:05:12,380 --> 00:05:14,540
What is our code word?

80
00:05:17,740 --> 00:05:19,900
Where are the encrypted messages
we exchanged?

81
00:05:21,260 --> 00:05:21,620
Uh...

82
00:05:22,020 --> 00:05:23,620
He's not from the Sparks Society.

83
00:05:24,420 --> 00:05:25,860
Now that you're a traitor,

84
00:05:26,580 --> 00:05:28,180
don't try to leave a good name behind.

85
00:05:29,140 --> 00:05:30,980
You try to drag me down
to save yourself,

86
00:05:31,740 --> 00:05:33,900
but you don't want your organization
to take you out.

87
00:05:34,900 --> 00:05:36,780
Wouldn't that be too good to be true?

88
00:05:36,780 --> 00:05:38,340
How would I know

89
00:05:38,340 --> 00:05:40,300
you won't kill me if I tell you?

90
00:05:40,300 --> 00:05:41,940
I will kill you anyway if you don't.

91
00:05:44,260 --> 00:05:45,620
But before that,

92
00:05:46,260 --> 00:05:48,060
I'll skin you alive.

93
00:06:01,140 --> 00:06:02,020
This person

94
00:06:02,300 --> 00:06:04,300
is related to you.

95
00:06:05,940 --> 00:06:08,540
He is Chu Yunfan,
the Young Leader of the Qing Gang.

96
00:06:08,900 --> 00:06:11,380
He's a high-level undercover agent
for the Beizhou government.

97
00:06:12,780 --> 00:06:14,060
What evidence do you have?

98
00:06:14,460 --> 00:06:17,580
Xiangyang Clinic
is our rendezvous point.

99
00:06:17,580 --> 00:06:19,740
You'll find everything you want there.

100
00:06:29,780 --> 00:06:30,620
Did you hear it?

101
00:06:32,380 --> 00:06:33,140
Yes.

102
00:07:02,300 --> 00:07:03,620
Chu Yunfan has been exposed.

103
00:07:04,060 --> 00:07:05,100
Ask him to escape now.

104
00:07:12,180 --> 00:07:13,100
Mohan.

105
00:07:17,980 --> 00:07:18,860
Who are these people?

106
00:07:20,940 --> 00:07:22,180
The shipment is arriving soon.

107
00:07:22,180 --> 00:07:23,860
All forces are stirring.

108
00:07:23,860 --> 00:07:26,500
So my father got us good people
to guard us.

109
00:07:29,700 --> 00:07:31,020
Are they here to guard

110
00:07:31,020 --> 00:07:32,380
or monitor?

111
00:07:33,780 --> 00:07:34,860
What are you talking about?

112
00:07:34,860 --> 00:07:36,860
It's just a precaution

113
00:07:36,860 --> 00:07:38,380
to keep us safe.

114
00:07:38,380 --> 00:07:40,460
Even the Marshal has agreed.

115
00:07:41,340 --> 00:07:42,140
Are you saying

116
00:07:42,660 --> 00:07:43,900
I should thank you?

117
00:07:50,570 --> 00:07:53,220
[You've been exposed. Escape now.]

118
00:08:10,260 --> 00:08:11,780
He's been shot and won't get far.

119
00:08:12,020 --> 00:08:12,740
Chase him down!

120
00:08:27,060 --> 00:08:28,100
The city has been locked down.

121
00:08:28,820 --> 00:08:30,700
Chihoko has been watching me too.

122
00:08:30,980 --> 00:08:32,220
It's hard to rescue him.

123
00:08:37,660 --> 00:08:38,340
Then

124
00:08:38,620 --> 00:08:39,660
leave me an exit

125
00:08:39,820 --> 00:08:40,980
at one of these stations.

126
00:08:41,580 --> 00:08:42,300
I'll do it.

127
00:08:46,100 --> 00:08:46,900
Emotionally,

128
00:08:47,260 --> 00:08:48,980
I don't want you to take this risk.

129
00:08:49,460 --> 00:08:50,420
But out of comradeship,

130
00:08:51,260 --> 00:08:53,500
I can only watch you go.

131
00:08:58,220 --> 00:08:59,140
Over the years,

132
00:09:00,460 --> 00:09:01,580
I've been struggling

133
00:09:01,580 --> 00:09:03,540
between personal emotions
and comradeship.

134
00:09:04,380 --> 00:09:06,180
It's nearly torn me apart.

135
00:09:17,340 --> 00:09:19,220
When I saw that undercover agent today,

136
00:09:20,460 --> 00:09:21,940
it felt like seeing myself.

137
00:09:23,660 --> 00:09:24,660
Perhaps one day,

138
00:09:24,780 --> 00:09:26,620
I might end up in that chair,

139
00:09:27,660 --> 00:09:28,740
being interrogated.

140
00:09:33,420 --> 00:09:34,460
We

141
00:09:35,060 --> 00:09:36,660
lurk in the dark

142
00:09:37,340 --> 00:09:38,540
so more people

143
00:09:38,540 --> 00:09:40,100
can live in the light.

144
00:09:42,060 --> 00:09:43,700
We are lucky

145
00:09:44,260 --> 00:09:45,580
because, at this moment,

146
00:09:46,020 --> 00:09:47,340
we can still hold each other

147
00:09:47,740 --> 00:09:49,020
and feel each other's heartbeat.

148
00:09:57,420 --> 00:09:59,260
Maybe it's because
I've met the one I love

149
00:10:00,340 --> 00:10:02,740
and I've got something to hold onto,

150
00:10:04,740 --> 00:10:06,860
that I've started to fear death.

151
00:10:07,860 --> 00:10:08,780
I'm afraid

152
00:10:09,620 --> 00:10:11,140
I won't be able to say goodbye to you.

153
00:10:12,500 --> 00:10:13,940
Then let's live every day

154
00:10:14,220 --> 00:10:16,140
as if it were our last.

155
00:10:17,100 --> 00:10:18,060
This way,

156
00:10:18,820 --> 00:10:20,100
even if we die,

157
00:10:20,660 --> 00:10:22,140
there won't be any regrets.

158
00:10:45,900 --> 00:10:47,540
Follow my order!

159
00:10:48,340 --> 00:10:50,180
Search every house.

160
00:10:50,900 --> 00:10:52,300
If anyone resists,

161
00:10:52,860 --> 00:10:53,900
kill them.

162
00:10:54,100 --> 00:10:54,980
Yes, sir.

163
00:11:09,180 --> 00:11:09,980
Stop the car.

164
00:11:14,140 --> 00:11:15,140
Deputy Shen.

165
00:11:22,420 --> 00:11:23,260
That was close.

166
00:11:23,820 --> 00:11:24,940
Luckily, we got prepared.

167
00:12:11,940 --> 00:12:12,540
Come on.

168
00:12:14,540 --> 00:12:15,500
- Let's go.
- Anning.

169
00:12:20,180 --> 00:12:20,820
Qinghuan,

170
00:12:21,300 --> 00:12:22,180
A thank you would be too small.

171
00:12:22,460 --> 00:12:23,540
I will thank you when I can.

172
00:12:25,220 --> 00:12:25,940
Let's go.

173
00:12:26,340 --> 00:12:28,060
Okay. I got it.

174
00:12:31,100 --> 00:12:33,780
I can't believe
Chu Yunfan managed to run.

175
00:12:36,300 --> 00:12:38,140
When did Yu Qinghuan leave the house?

176
00:12:39,780 --> 00:12:42,060
Around 5 PM.

177
00:12:43,820 --> 00:12:46,060
That's too much of a coincidence.

178
00:12:48,260 --> 00:12:50,780
She is close to Chu Yunfan.

179
00:12:51,100 --> 00:12:52,900
Now that Chu Yunfan
is an undercover agent,

180
00:12:54,020 --> 00:12:56,740
she probably has another identity too.

181
00:13:11,020 --> 00:13:12,220
Please help me.

182
00:13:22,470 --> 00:13:25,270
[Joys of Life Dancing Hall]

183
00:14:02,420 --> 00:14:06,140
♪The waves♪

184
00:14:06,220 --> 00:14:10,420
♪When will you stop
looking through them?♪

185
00:14:10,500 --> 00:14:14,460
♪Missed the time
when the sun was restored♪

186
00:14:14,540 --> 00:14:18,620
♪What else do you expect to like?♪

187
00:14:18,660 --> 00:14:21,380
♪I thought you were an angel♪

188
00:14:21,460 --> 00:14:23,660
♪An angel who watched over me♪

189
00:14:23,700 --> 00:14:26,740
♪And saw every side of me♪

190
00:14:26,820 --> 00:14:29,380
♪Until reality is flooded♪

191
00:14:29,460 --> 00:14:31,620
♪You become sensible♪

192
00:14:31,700 --> 00:14:36,180
♪You are finally
out of touch with reality♪

193
00:14:36,500 --> 00:14:39,020
♪I hear the mountains, the seas,
and the people♪

194
00:14:39,100 --> 00:14:41,060
♪All clamoring because of you♪

195
00:14:41,180 --> 00:14:43,140
♪Hiding in the cape after the rain♪

196
00:14:43,300 --> 00:14:45,580
♪I cannot hear you♪

197
00:14:45,620 --> 00:14:49,100
♪So I opened my arms one last time♪

198
00:14:49,260 --> 00:14:52,620
♪But you escaped through the gap♪

199
00:14:52,740 --> 00:14:54,940
♪I saw winters come and summers go♪

200
00:14:54,980 --> 00:14:57,100
♪And thought there was ample time♪

201
00:14:57,340 --> 00:14:59,140
♪Cannot withstand the waves♪

202
00:14:59,260 --> 00:15:01,220
♪But you always make me panic♪

203
00:15:01,300 --> 00:15:05,540
♪How ridiculous, making me learn♪

204
00:15:05,620 --> 00:15:08,900
♪How much I am worth♪
